{"@context":"http://iiif.io/api/presentation/3/context.json","id":"https://digbmc.github.io/pta-manifests/phan/phan-14034/manifest.json","type":"Manifest","label":{"none":["PHAN-14034"]},"metadata":[{"label":{"none":["Timestamp"]},"value":{"none":["1:40:34"]}},{"label":{"none":["Film"]},"value":{"none":["Phantom Thread"]}},{"label":{"none":["Distance"]},"value":{"none":["close-up"]}},{"label":{"none":["Angle"]},"value":{"none":["low, over the shoulder"]}},{"label":{"none":["Location"]},"value":{"none":["interior"]}},{"label":{"none":["Movement"]},"value":{"none":["fixed"]}},{"label":{"none":["Composition"]},"value":{"none":["single shot"]}}],"summary":{"none":["A man looks at a woman seated across from him."]},"thumbnail":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-14034/tiles/full/300,169/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":169,"width":300}],"homepage":[{"id":"PHAN-14034","type":"Text","format":"text/html","label":{"none":["Object homepage"]}}],"items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-14034/canvas/1","type":"Canvas","height":1080,"width":1920,"label":{"none":["PHAN-14034"]},"thumbnail":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-14034/tiles/full/300,169/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":169,"width":300}],"items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-14034/canvas/1/annopage-1","type":"AnnotationPage","items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-14034/canvas/1/annopage-1/anno-1","type":"Annotation","motivation":"painting","target":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-14034/canvas/1","body":{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-14034/tiles/full/1920,1080/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":1080,"width":1920,"service":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-14034/tiles","type":"ImageService3","profile":"http://iiif.io/api/image/3/level0.json"}]}}]}],"annotations":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-14034/canvas/1/page/p1","type":"AnnotationPage","items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-14034/canvas/1/051cd91d-08b8-4608-a04b-6348fcf58692","type":"Annotation","motivation":"commenting","body":[{"created":"2026-07-01T14:57:09.082Z","creator":"lucia","purpose":"commenting","type":"TextualBody","format":"text/html","value":"<p>PTA had the following to say about Reynolds’s character in the press materials for the film: “‘Reynolds is a man who is completely self-consumed, self-contained, self-aware and self-regimented,’ says Anderson. ‘As script and character took form, I became more and more interested in exploring what kind of man might live inside such a structure. A character requiring that level of control is ripe for being dismantled. What happens when a man like that becomes weak for the first time, or discovers that he needs somebody?’” (“About the Production,” 9). This internal struggle is readily apparent in this scene, as Reynolds attempts to remain in control—of himself and of his relationship with Alma—even as her behaviors annoy him.&nbsp;</p>"}],"target":{"type":"SpecificResource","source":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-14034/canvas/1","selector":{"type":"FragmentSelector","conformsTo":"http://www.w3.org/TR/media-frags/","value":"xywh=pixel:751.9480519480519,74.02597402597394,621.0389610389611,781.5584415584417"}}}]}]}]}